2609	[Section coherence of the affine immersion $\mathrm{fromSpec}$]
2610	  \label{lem:fromSpec_image_top_section_coherence}
2611	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.fromSpec_image_top_section_coherence}
2612	  \uses{def:gamma_image_ring_equiv}
2613	  Let \(X\) be a scheme and \(U \subseteq X\) an affine open, with canonical affine immersion
2614	  \(\mathrm{fromSpec} : \Spec \Gamma(X, U) \to X\) of image \(U\), and write
2615	  \(e_{\top} : \mathrm{fromSpec}\,''^{U}\,\top = U\) for the canonical identification of its image
2616	  with \(U\). Let
2617	  \(\sigma = (\Gamma\Spec\text{-iso})^{-1} \circ \mathrm{gammaImageRingEquiv}\,\mathrm{fromSpec}\,\top\)
2618	  (\cref{def:gamma_image_ring_equiv}) be the \(\top\)-level section ring isomorphism, and let
2619	  \(\rho : \mathcal{O}_X(U) \xrightarrow{\sim} \mathcal{O}_X(\mathrm{fromSpec}''^{U}\,\top)\) be the
2620	  structure-sheaf isomorphism induced by \(e_{\top}\). Then \(\rho \circ \sigma = \mathrm{id}\), i.e.,
2621	  \(\rho(\sigma\,f) = f\) for every \(f \in \Gamma(X, U)\).
2622	\end{lemma}
2623	\begin{proof}
2624	  The composite \(\rho \circ \sigma\) is a ring endomorphism of \(\Gamma(X, U)\). Expanding the
2625	  definition of \(\sigma\) via \cref{def:gamma_image_ring_equiv} and applying the self-application
2626	  identity of \(\mathrm{fromSpec}\) over \(U\)---which identifies the image of the total open of
2627	  \(\Spec\Gamma(X,U)\) under \(\mathrm{fromSpec}\) with \(U\)---together with presheaf naturality,
2628	  the composite \(\rho \circ \sigma\) reduces to a \(\Gamma(X,U)\)-algebra endomorphism of
2629	  \(\Gamma(X,U)\). Since the only such endomorphism is the identity, \(\rho(\sigma\,f) = f\).
2630	\end{proof}
